<task id="AUTHV2-028" project="Spaarke Auth v2 + Hardening">
  <metadata>
    <title>Verify + rebuild all PCFs against @spaarke/auth v2</title>
    <phase>B — Consumer migration</phase>
    <tags>auth, pcf, STANDARD</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 hour</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>Phase A</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>B-Parallel-2</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>PCFs (UniversalDatasetGrid, UniversalQuickCreate, SpeDocumentViewer, others) already use @spaarke/auth correctly per audit. Verify no compile errors from v2 library changes, rebuild + redeploy each. Critical for INV-8 (bundling reality).</prompt>
  <role>PCF deployment engineer.</role>
  <goal>Every PCF rebuilt against @spaarke/auth v2 and redeployed. No PCF stays on old library (would cause popup regression).</goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/client/pcf/UniversalDatasetGrid/</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/UniversalQuickCreate/</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/SpeDocumentViewer/</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/pcf-deploy/SKILL.md (deploy procedure)</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>List all PCFs in src/client/pcf/. For each: run npm run build:prod (NOT npm run build — see CLAUDE.md AP-1).</step>
    <step>If any fail compile, fix usage to match v2 API (likely just import path changes).</step>
    <step>Run pcf-deploy skill for each PCF to push solution ZIP to Dataverse dev environment.</step>
    <step>Verify in browser that each PCF loads without popup (MSAL regression check).</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Every PCF builds with npm run build:prod (production mode).</criterion>
    <criterion>Every PCF deployed to dev Dataverse environment.</criterion>
    <criterion>MSAL regression test passes on each PCF.</criterion>
    <criterion>No PCF references the OLD @spaarke/auth API.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
